title: PLAZA / TIRETRACKS VISCAL
description: You notice a set of a motor carriage tracks backing into the fence.

dialogueTree.title: Visual Calculus: "The tracks are as they have ever be..."
dialogueTree.english: The tracks are as they have ever been. A bit more worn, perhaps. Fortunately, the street sweeper still hasn't noticed their presence.
dialogueTree.polish: Ślady są dokładnie takie, jak i wcześniej. Może odrobinę mniej wyraźne. Szczęśliwie sprzątacze jeszcze ich nie zauważyli.
dialogueTree.belarusian: Сляды дакладна такія ж, што і раней. Магчыма, крыху менш выразныя. На шчасце, дворнік іх ўсё яшчэ не заўважыў.

links.title: You: ""A car drove through the fence.""
links.english: "A car drove through the fence."
links.polish: „Przez płot przejechał samochód”.
links.belarusian: "Праз плот праехаў аўтамабіль".

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You are correct. This is a rather..."
links.english: "You are correct. This is a rather motor carriage-friendly city."
links.polish: „Zgadza się. To miasto jest dość przyjazne powozom motorowym”.
links.belarusian: "Вы маеце рацыю. Гэты горад даволі прыязны да маторных карэт".

links.title: Inland Empire: "Somehow that makes you feel... scar..."
links.english: Somehow that makes you feel... scared. You don't know why.
links.polish: Z jakiegoś powodu budzi to twój... strach. Nie wiesz czemu.
links.belarusian: Чамусьці гэта выклікае ў цябе... страх. Ты не ведаеш чаму.

links.title: You: ""Is this connected to the case?""
links.english: "Is this connected to the case?"
links.polish: „Czy to ma jakiś związek ze sprawą?”
links.belarusian: "Ці мае гэта нейкае дачыненне да справы?"

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""I'm not sure... there are plenty o..."
links.english: "I'm not sure... there are plenty of traffic accidents waiting to happen in Martinaise. With the jam right here on the roundabout. I would keep them separate."
links.polish: „Nie jestem pewny... W Martinaise dochodzi do wielu wypadków komunikacyjnych. Zwłaszcza z tym korkiem na rondzie. Nie łączyłbym tych dwóch spraw”.
links.belarusian: "Я не ўпэўнены... У Марцінэзе адбываецца шмат транспартных здарэнняў. Асабліва з тым заторам на развязцы. Я бы разглядаў гэтыя выпадкі паасобку".

links.title: Visual Calculus: "You could *follow* the tracks south..."
links.english: You could *follow* the tracks south. There seems to be a canal there. See where they went. (If you find the time.)
links.polish: Mógłbyś *ruszyć* za śladami na południe. Jest tam, zdaje się, kanał. Możesz sprawdzić, dokąd prowadzą (jeśli znajdziesz na to czas).
links.belarusian: Ты мог бы *пайсці* па слядах на поўдзень. Там, здаецца, ёсць канал. Можаш праверыць, куды яны вядуць (калі знойдзеш на гэта час).

links.title: You: ""This is where I started off with m..."
links.english: "This is where I started off with my motor carriage... before sinking it in the sea."
links.polish: „To stąd ruszyłem swoim powozem motorowym... zanim utopiłem go w morzu”.
links.belarusian: "Адсюль я выправіўся на сваёй маторнай карэце... перш чым патапіць яе ў моры".

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""No wonder the cafeteria manager se..."
links.english: "No wonder the cafeteria manager seemed frustrated when he was giving us directions to the yard."
links.polish: „Nic dziwnego, że kierownik baru był taki sfrustrowany, gdy tłumaczył nam, jak dotrzeć na ten dziedziniec”.
links.belarusian: "Не дзіва, што кіраўнік бара выглядаў засмучаным, калі тлумачыў нам, як дабрацца ў двор".

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Well," he gestures toward the gapi..."
links.english: "Well," he gestures toward the gaping hole in the fence, "you did provide us with a very convenient access point to the crime scene."
links.polish: „Cóż...” – wskazuje wielki otwór w ogrodzeniu – „...zapewniłeś nam bardzo wygodny dostęp do miejsca zbrodni”.
links.belarusian: "Ну... — ён паказвае на вялікую дзірку ў плоце. — Вы забяспечылі нам вельмі зручны доступ да месца злачынства".

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yes, it is. Well," he gestures tow..."
links.english: "Yes, it is. Well," he gestures toward the gaping hole in the fence, "you did provide us with a very convenient access point to the crime scene."
links.polish: „Zgadza się. Cóż...” – wskazuje wielki otwór w ogrodzeniu – „...zapewniłeś nam bardzo wygodny dostęp do miejsca zbrodni”.
links.belarusian: "Сапраўды. Ну... — ён паказвае на вялікую дзірку ў плоце. — Вы забяспечылі нам вельмі зручны доступ да месца злачынства".

links.title: You: ""This is the point of departure of..."
links.english: "This is the point of departure of the vehicle that crashed into the Samaran Butter sign."
links.polish: „Z tego miejsca ruszył pojazd, który rozbił się o znak reklamujący samarskie masło”.
links.belarusian: "З гэтага месца выехаў аўтамабіль, які ўрэзаўся ў шчыт з рэкламай самарскага масла".

links.title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant follows the tracks w..."
links.english: The lieutenant follows the tracks with his gaze. "That's plausible. A similar... reckless abandon seems to be in evidence."
links.polish: Porucznik podąża wzrokiem za śladami kół. „To prawdopodobne. Widać tu... podobną lekkomyślną beztroskę”.
links.belarusian: Лейтэнант праходзіцца позіркам па слядах колаў: "Гэта верагодна. Яўна... тая ж легкадумная бестурботнасць".

links.title: You: "I think I got it. [Leave.]"
links.english: I think I got it. [Leave.]
links.polish: „Chyba już wszystko wiem”. [Odejdź].
links.belarusian: "Здаецца, я зразумеў". [Адысці.]

links.title: You: "This is significant somehow."
links.english: This is significant somehow.
links.polish: To z jakiegoś powodu istotne.
links.belarusian: Гэта чамусьці важна.

links.title: Visual Calculus: "Maybe. Probably."
links.english: Maybe. Probably.
links.polish: Może. Prawdopodobnie.
links.belarusian: Можа. Верагодна.

links.title: Inland Empire: "An ominous warning of bad things ah..."
links.english: An ominous warning of bad things ahead.
links.polish: Ponure ostrzeżenie przed czekającym cię złem.
links.belarusian: Злавесная перасцярога пра благое, што чакае наперадзе.

links.title: You: "This is where I started off with my..."
links.english: This is where I started off with my motor carriage.
links.polish: To stąd ruszyłem swoim powozem motorowym.
links.belarusian: Адсюль я выправіўся на сваёй моторнай карэце.

links.title: Visual Calculus: "Yes. And ended up half-sunken in th..."
links.english: Yes. And ended up half-sunken in the sea. You must have been drunk when you left off.
links.polish: Tak. A skończyłeś na wpół utopiony w morzu. Musiałeś być pijany, kiedy ruszałeś.
links.belarusian: Так. А закончыў напалову патопленым ў моры. Мусіць, ты быў п'яны, калі выехаў.

links.title: You: "This is the point of departure of t..."
links.english: This is the point of departure of the motor carriage that crashed into the Samaran Butter sign, right?
links.polish: Z tego miejsca ruszył powóz motorowy, który rozbił się o znak reklamujący samarskie masło, tak?
links.belarusian: З гэтага месца выехала маторная карэта, якая ўрэзалася ў шчыт з рэкламай самарскага масла, так?

links.title: Visual Calculus: "Why yes it is! Good connection."
links.english: Why yes it is! Good connection.
links.polish: Właśnie tak! Dobrze to powiązałeś.
links.belarusian: Дакладна так! Добра ты гэта звязаў.

dialogueTree.title: Perception (Sight): "You see a set of tyre tracks in the..."
dialogueTree.english: You see a set of tyre tracks in the brown slush that covers the plaza mosaic.
dialogueTree.polish: W brązowej mazi pokrywającej mozaikę placu widzisz ślady opon.
dialogueTree.belarusian: У бурай гразі, што пакрывае мазаіку пляца, ты бачыш сляды шын.

links.title: You: "Why am I looking at this?"
links.english: Why am I looking at this?
links.polish: Czemu ja zwracam na to uwagę?
links.belarusian: Чаму я звяртаю на гэта ўвагу?

links.title: Perception (Sight): "Cop habit. You look at everything."
links.english: Cop habit. You look at everything.
links.polish: Policyjne nawyki. Zwracasz uwagę na wszystko.
links.belarusian: Паліцэйская звычка. Ты звяртаеш увагу на ўсё.

links.title: Logic: "This isn't case-related, you think."
links.english: This isn't case-related, you think.
links.polish: To nie ma związku ze sprawą – myślisz.
links.belarusian: Гэта не мае дачынення да справы, — думаеш ты.

links.title: You: "What kind of vehicle drove through..."
links.english: What kind of vehicle drove through here?
links.polish: Jaki pojazd mógł tędy przejechać?
links.belarusian: Які транспартны сродак тут праехаў?

links.title: Perception (Sight): "Hard to say."
links.english: Hard to say.
links.polish: Trudno powiedzieć.
links.belarusian: Цяжка сказаць.

links.title: Perception (Sight): "Hard to say. Your vision is blurred..."
links.english: Hard to say. Your vision is blurred and you are having difficulty concentrating thanks to your relentless hangover.
links.polish: Trudno powiedzieć. Przez nieustępującego kaca nie widzisz zbyt wyraźnie i masz problemy z koncentracją.
links.belarusian: Цяжка сказаць. Праз несуцішнае пахмелле ты не бачыш надта ясна і маеш праблемы з канцэнтрацыяй.

links.title: You: "Reconstruct the movement."
links.english: Reconstruct the movement.
links.polish: Odtwórz ruch pojazdu.
links.belarusian: Рэканструяваць перамяшчэнне.

links.title: Visual Calculus: "The tyre tracks were left here by a..."
links.english: The tyre tracks were left here by an unknown event that took place some days ago. It's a message, written in the language of burnt rubber.
links.polish: Ślady opon zostały tu jako pamiątka po nieznanym wydarzeniu sprzed kilku dni. To zapisana językiem spalonej gumy wiadomość.
links.belarusian: Сляды шын засталіся тут як напамін аб невядомай падзеі некалькі дзён таму. Гэта паведамленне, запісанае мовай спаленай гумы.

links.title: Visual Calculus: "Some of that rubber stuck to the ti..."
links.english: Some of that rubber stuck to the tiles right in front of the Whirling-in-Rags. This is point A. The driver started there...
links.polish: Nieco tej gumy przylgnęło do płytek tuż przy wejściu do Whirling-in-Rags. To punkt A. Kierowca stał tutaj...
links.belarusian: Шматок гэтай гумы прыляпіўся да пліткі адразу пры ўваходзе ў Whirling-in-Rags. Гэта пункт А. Кіроўца ад'ехаў адсюль...

links.title: Visual Calculus: "...and then accelerated straight in..."
links.english: ...and then accelerated straight into the fence.
links.polish: ...a potem ruszył i wjechał prosto w płot.
links.belarusian: ...а потым рушыў і наўпрост урэзаўся ў плот.

Alternate1.english: ...and then accelerated straight into the fence. Left a hole *big enough for the Franconigerian cavalry,* according to the cafeteria manager.
Alternate1.polish: ...a potem ruszył i wjechał prosto w płot. Jak twierdzi kierownik baru, zostawił dziurę taką, że *zmieściłaby się w niej frankonigeryjska kawaleria*.
Alternate1.belarusian: ...а потым рушыў і наўпрост урэзаўся ў плот. Пакінуў дзірку *дастаткова вялікую, каб праз яе магла праехаць Франканігерыйская кавалерыя*, як сцвярджае кіраўнік бара

Alternate2.english: ...and then accelerated straight into the fence. Left a hole *big enough for the Franconigerian cavalry,* according to the cafeteria manager. (Why that pang of guilt again?)
Alternate2.polish: ...a potem ruszył i wjechał prosto w płot. Jak twierdzi kierownik baru, zostawił dziurę taką, że *zmieściłaby się w niej frankonigeryjska kawaleria*. Skąd znów to poczucie winy?
Alternate2.belarusian: ...а потым рушыў і наўпрост урэзаўся ў плот. Пакінуў дзірку *дастаткова вялікую, каб праз яе магла праехаць Франканігерыйская кавалерыя*, як сцвярджае кіраўнік бара. (Адкуль зноў гэта пачуццё віны?)

links.title: Authority: "The hole in this fence doesn't look..."
links.english: The hole in this fence doesn't look *that* huge.
links.polish: Dziura w tym płocie nie wygląda na *aż tak* wielką.
links.belarusian: Дзірка ў гэтым плоце не выглядае *настолькі* вялікай.

links.title: You: "Damn bartender."
links.english: Damn bartender.
links.polish: Przeklęty barman.
links.belarusian: Кляты бармэн.

links.title: Authority: "He was exaggerating. People blame *..."
links.english: He was exaggerating. People blame *cops* for everything that goes wrong in the world. This has nothing to do with you.
links.polish: Przesadzał. Ludzie winią *policję* za całe zło tego świata. To nie ma nic wspólnego z tobą konkretnie.
links.belarusian: Ён перабольшыў. Людзі вінавацяць *копаў* ва ўсім зле гэтага свету. З табой гэта ніяк не звязана.

links.title: Interfacing: "As a matter of fact, you don't even..."
links.english: As a matter of fact, you don't even know why you stopped here. You would never drive recklessly like this. And you don't have a car.
links.polish: Prawdę mówiąc, nie wiesz nawet, czemu się tu zatrzymałeś. Przecież nie jeździłbyś tak lekkomyślnie. W dodatku nie masz samochodu.
links.belarusian: Папраўдзе, ты нават не ведаеш, чаму тут спыніўся. Ты ніколі не вёў бы настолькі легкадумна. Да таго ж у цябе нямае машыны.

links.title: You: "The hole is not that impressive."
links.english: The hole is not that impressive.
links.polish: Dziura nie jest aż tak niesamowita.
links.belarusian: Дзірка не так уж моцна ўражвае.

links.title: You: "Okay. What happened next?"
links.english: Okay. What happened next?
links.polish: Dobrze. Co się stało później?
links.belarusian: Добра. Што адбылося пазней?

links.title: You: "What happened next?"
links.english: What happened next?
links.polish: Co się stało później?
links.belarusian: Што адбылося пазней?

links.title: Visual Calculus: "The driver proceeded to back out of..."
links.english: The driver proceeded to back out of the yard, barely stopping before hitting the adjacent building...
links.polish: Kierowca wycofał się potem z podwórza i nieznacznie tylko zwolnił, zanim uderzył w sąsiedni budynek...
links.belarusian: Кіроўца з'ехаў з двара і ледзь запаволіў рух перад тым, як урэзацца ў сумежны будынак...

links.title: Visual Calculus: "...before heading south. Must have..."
links.english: ...before heading south. Must have been in a hurry.
links.polish: ...po czym ruszył na południe. Musiał się spieszyć.
links.belarusian: ...пасля чаго накіраваўся на ​​поўдзень. Ён, пэўна, спяшаўся.

links.title: Visual Calculus: "No, these tracks are not interestin..."
links.english: No, these tracks are not interesting at all. Let the street sweeper just sweep them away.
links.polish: Nie, te ślady nie są ani trochę interesujące. Niech sprzątacze je po prostu zmiotą.
links.belarusian: Не, гэтыя сляды зусім не цікавыя. Няхай дворнік іх проста прыбярэ.

links.title: You: "Not now. [Leave.]"
links.english: Not now. [Leave.]
links.polish: Nie teraz. [Odejdź].
links.belarusian: Не зараз. [Адысці.]
